        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough | Kent</placeName>
                    <date>March 15<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for your note, informing me that you have at length found a purchaser of the £600 Shrewsbury St. Act.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I presume you will want the enclosed Transfers: anyhow I send them: I understand that I have to pay Transfer fee.— I presume I shall receive the half-years interest due on the 28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. inst.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I do not know whether M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Wigley is aware that my Bankers, are M<hi rend="superscript">s</hi> Robarts. Curtis &amp; Co.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I am much obliged for your assistance &amp; remain | My dear Sir | Very truly yours | C. R. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">T. Salt Esq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 600£] ‘£’ <hi rend="italic">above</hi> ‘600’</note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.3 I understand … fee.—] <hi rend="italic">added</hi></note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.4 inst.] <hi rend="italic">over dash</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is supplied from the wrapper containing this letter, which is labelled ‘28 M<hi rend="superscript">ch</hi> 1853’ (see n. 3, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Salt’s letter has not been found; see also this volume, Supplement, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1499F.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Thomas Salt, 31 January [1853]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">There is a draft transfer in the Shropshire Archives (SA D3651/B/47/2/30). In his Investment book (Down House MS), pp. 1–2, CD recorded an interest payment on 28 March 1853, but did not record any transfer fees.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7832.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Wigley</ref> was an accountant working with Salt. See also this volume, Supplement, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1507F.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Charles Wigley, 21 March 1853</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
